1
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:52,620
=Lucky's First Love=

2
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:55,620
=Episode 3=

3
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,040
Let me tell you a secret.

4
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,600
My first girlfriend

5
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,010
was a kendo coach.

6
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:05,650
So I am quite experienced at this.

7
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:09,540
Did you often help her with this?

8
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,270
I helped myself.

9
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,160
Ah?

10
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:24,120
You mustn't tell anyone else
or your annual bonus will be canceled.

11
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:29,940
Mr. Xia, can you practice kendo?

12
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:31,960
A little bit.

13
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,760
Do you know any move

14
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:35,840
that can give bad guys a deadly blow?

15
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,910
If you want to defeat bad guys at a time,

16
00:02:39,910 --> 00:02:42,600
I suppose the best move
is to kick their crotches

17
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,200
and play it by ear afterwards.

18
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,440
I see.

19
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:57,120
When... did you shower last time?

20
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,480
I... I have a shower every day.

21
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,080
Then what's this?

22
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:08,610
Ju... just sweat, okay?

23
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,800
How can people not sweat

24
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,600
after running on mud all day
and struggling to survive?

25
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,400
Gift on the first meeting?

26
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,880
How did you know?

27
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:30,580
Mr. Xia, since you're well informed,

28
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:31,700
can you have another look

29
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:33,670
and tell me whether this bracelet
is expensive or not?

30
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,400
Not valuable at all.

31
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,760
As cheap as a scooter.

32
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,360
Really?

33
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,700
Hurry up.

34
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,560
It hurts.

35
00:03:57,760 --> 00:03:58,290
Oh.

36
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,640
Are you okay?

37
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:01,480
I'm fine.

38
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,650
Mr. Xia... I'm sorry.

39
00:04:05,650 --> 00:04:06,500
Are you okay?

40
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,840
Sorry.

41
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:16,800
I wasn't on purpose.

42
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:26,440
Fine, I'll wear it
since we can't take it off.

43
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,420
Can I take a shower?

44
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,570
As you wish.

45
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:47,560
Put it on after the shower.

46
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,430
Woman's clothes.

47
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,400
Your girlfriend's?

48
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,430
None of your business.

49
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,810
Just take it.

50
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,250
Be careful during the shower.

51
00:04:57,760 --> 00:04:59,430
If you fall over because of your injured ankle,

52
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:00,640
I can't come in to help you.

53
00:05:01,670 --> 00:05:02,200
Oh.

54
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:04,280
Thank you, Mr. Xia.

55
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:26,480
(Chu Nan, are you asleep? A lot happened today.
Forget it. I will tell you next time. Good night.)

56
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,600
Mr. Xia, don't bother.

57
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:41,200
It's okay for me to sleep in the guest room.

58
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:53,830
Is this truly your guest room?

59
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,080
There is nothing here.

60
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,180
Because I don't like other people
sleeping in my house.

61
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,280
So where will you sleep?

62
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,680
On the sofa.

63
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,720
Well, I can sleep there.

64
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:08,760
Yeah. You sleep on the sofa.

65
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:11,030
But at night, I usually

66
00:06:11,030 --> 00:06:12,960
get up to drink some water or sleepwalk.

67
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:14,720
You'd better cover yourself up well.

68
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,200
Slee... sleepwalk?

69
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:22,390
Fine. I'm injured.

70
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:24,960
Sorry to make you sleep on the sofa.

71
00:06:27,830 --> 00:06:30,000
I feel sleepy all of a sudden.
Wanna go to bed now.

72
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,440
There is a glass of hot milk near the bed.

73
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:35,160
Drink it before you go to sleep.

74
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:36,960
Thank you, Mr. Xia.

75
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,360
(Chu Nan, are you asleep? A lot happened today.
Forget it. I will tell you next time. Good night.)

76
00:07:17,590 --> 00:07:19,030
Sorry Xing Yun.

77
00:07:19,030 --> 00:07:20,950
I was watching a midnight movie with my husband

78
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:22,560
and missed your call.

79
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,280
Are you all right?

80
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:25,700
How was your day?

81
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,910
It's a long story.

82
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:35,120
Sounds like something big happened.

83
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,620
By the way, I'll send you an article
of relationship advice

84
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:39,250
which is of great use to you at present.

85
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:41,220
It can help know better about him.

86
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,900
Let's talk about other details at the company.

87
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:43,640
Good night!

88
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:46,200
Relationship advice?

89
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,120
Ten things you must check

90
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,160
during the first visit to your boyfriend's.

91
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:58,840
What?

92
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,910
His room

93
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:04,200
reveals his real personalities.

94
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,450
During the first visit to your boyfriend's,

95
00:08:06,450 --> 00:08:07,350
you can sum up his life trajectory

96
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:09,750
from his bedroom.

97
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:14,760
A man's bedding reflects his moral quality?

98
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:18,420
After all, each person spends
1/3 of his or her life

99
00:08:18,420 --> 00:08:20,000
staying in bed.

100
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,250
Therefore, the texture of his bedding
represents his moral quality

101
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:25,250
and patterns represent his taste.

102
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:29,060
How about the bedding

103
00:08:29,060 --> 00:08:31,110
in a cold solid color and made of cotton?

104
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:35,460
Simple, tasteful and of high quality.

105
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:37,030
Congratulations! You chose the right man.

106
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,330
He isn't the person I chose, okay?

107
00:08:39,330 --> 00:08:41,220
Next. The closet is the place

108
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:43,190
that hides a man's biggest secret of his life.

109
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:46,130
A man will do a spring-clean

110
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:47,440
before he invites his girlfriend to his house.

111
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,730
So only the cleanliness in his closet

112
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:51,650
can reflect what a person he truly is.

113
00:08:51,650 --> 00:08:53,830
Of course, the clothes a man chooses

114
00:08:53,830 --> 00:08:55,330
are also something worth studying.

115
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:57,090
If his closet is pretty empty,

116
00:08:57,090 --> 00:08:58,920
this man is rigid and dull.

117
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,150
If his closet

118
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:01,640
is like a fashion week,

119
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:03,240
you need to take greater caution.

120
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,160
Paying so much attention to dress himself up,

121
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:07,360
he definitely not only aims at you.

122
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,280
Mr. Xia indeed has severe OCD.

123
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,580
His dressing style is well matched with him.

124
00:09:14,580 --> 00:09:15,780
Though here are only a few types of clothes,

125
00:09:15,780 --> 00:09:17,940
all of them are high-end.

126
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:21,000
Congratulation again! You chose the right man.

127
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:26,710
If you happen to see several books in his room,

128
00:09:26,710 --> 00:09:28,130
no hurry to admire him.

129
00:09:28,130 --> 00:09:30,370
Open the books to check they are for showing off

130
00:09:30,370 --> 00:09:31,720
or for reading.

131
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,400
I prefer comic books.

132
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:40,560
Anyway, however perfect he is

133
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:41,720
up till now,

134
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,650
there is one most important thing

135
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:45,920
which can erase all of his perfection.

136
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,440
What's that?

137
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,310
Whether there are

138
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:54,690
woman's items in his room.

139
00:09:54,950 --> 00:09:56,660
Even a strand of long hair

140
00:09:56,950 --> 00:09:58,520
can overturn previous conclusions

141
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,320
and kick him out of your world at once.

142
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,660
No need to find. Look at what I wear.

143
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,860
I urge you to leave now.

144
00:10:07,860 --> 00:10:08,680
Or you'll get involved in

145
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,840
a fierce and bloody fight.

146
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,040
Are you kidding me?

147
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:19,720
Out of power?

148
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:26,000
What am I thinking about?

149
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:30,560
It's weird to sleep in boss's bed.

150
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,120
Let it go. Let it go.

151
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,960
I'll leave right after getting up tomorrow.

152
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,600
On a sunny afternoon,

153
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:43,360
a handsome boy lies on a lawn.

154
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:46,240
Suddenly, he closes his book. Do you know why?

155
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,200
A. It's going to rain so he has to leave.

156
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:52,240
B. He wants to sleep.

157
00:10:52,930 --> 00:10:55,240
C. He wants to read another book.

158
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,950
I choose B. He wants to sleep.

159
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,520
Then you are my Miss Right.

160
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:03,720
Come on.

161
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:04,920
I understand.

162
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,120
What you said is nonsense.

163
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:08,080
As long as you like it.

164
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,840
A man is like a book.

165
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,340
He can't understand himself.

166
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:19,000
Only women can.

167
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:21,810
Don't give up reading immediately

168
00:11:21,810 --> 00:11:23,880
if the preface is obscure.

169
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:25,750
Read it several times.

170
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,550
Perhaps you will find out the treasure.

171
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,120
Don't get immersed into it

172
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:34,120
if stories are full of ups and downs.

173
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,070
There are many

174
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:37,360
bad endings.

175
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,320
A smart woman needs to know

176
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:42,880
how to select a book at the same level
with her wisdom

177
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,840
so that she won't waste her time or youth.

178
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:48,920
When a woman happens to

179
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,600
open the book of me,

180
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:52,950
I will grab her,

181
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:54,560
make her keep reading

182
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,970
and finally station myself in her heart.

183
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,920
As to what the reader gets from this book,

184
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:01,000
it all depends on herself.

185
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:04,180
I really want to have a try.

186
00:12:21,730 --> 00:12:22,640
Where are we going?

187
00:12:27,910 --> 00:12:28,960
Wait...

188
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:34,980
Is... is there an earthquake?

189
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,020
Keep quiet.

190
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,630
Is he hiding from usurers?

191
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:43,890
Mr. Xia is so wealthy.

192
00:12:43,890 --> 00:12:45,840
Can't imagine he is dunned for debts.

193
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,690
Oh my!

194
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:48,400
Will there be fierce-looking gangsters

195
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,120
later chopping the closet door?

196
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,600
How unlucky I am!

197
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,010
I just survived from some human traffickers.

198
00:12:53,010 --> 00:12:54,960
Now I'm going to be killed by usurers.

199
00:13:00,370 --> 00:13:01,200
What have you done!

200
00:13:03,060 --> 00:13:05,120
I didn't dirty your hands on purpose.

201
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,090
I lick my lips when I'm nervous.

202
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:08,180
Shut up your mouth.

203
00:13:29,540 --> 00:13:32,630
Mr. Xia, I can't bear it any more.

204
00:13:32,630 --> 00:13:33,380
Keep bearing.

205
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:37,280
But my ankle really hurts.

206
00:13:41,060 --> 00:13:41,820
You must bear it.

207
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:43,350
Hold still.

208
00:13:43,350 --> 00:13:44,390
But I...

209
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,460
Why are you hiding here?

210
00:13:53,170 --> 00:13:54,820
Xiaoxi, go to the living room to play.

211
00:13:57,220 --> 00:14:00,580
Is this a new way to have fun?

212
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:03,010
Closet play?

213
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,840
Isn't this the lady I met
at that underwear store?

214
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:07,960
So embarrassing.

215
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,780
You misunderstood.

216
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:11,170
It's not what you think.

217
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,110
It's you.

218
00:14:13,110 --> 00:14:14,920
It's really not what you think.

219
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:18,150
Right!

220
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:20,070
I ran into some accidents yesterday

221
00:14:20,070 --> 00:14:22,180
and had no other choice
but to stay at Mr. Xia's.

222
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:23,880
Nothing happened between us.

223
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:25,120
Please trust Mr. Xia.

224
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,550
He is faithful to you.

225
00:14:26,550 --> 00:14:29,240
You're not eligible to tell me how he treats me.

226
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:30,960
I...

227
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,840
You gave her my pajama?

228
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:34,200
Enough...

229
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:35,890
I'm sorry.

230
00:14:37,190 --> 00:14:40,100
So what forced you to stay here?

231
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:43,840
Yesterday I truly ran into some accidents

232
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,840
which you might not believe.

233
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,810
I met human traffickers at first.

234
00:14:48,450 --> 00:14:49,810
Then I sprained my ankle

235
00:14:49,810 --> 00:14:51,240
and got my bag stolen.

236
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:53,010
Since my identification
and keys were all in that bag

237
00:14:53,860 --> 00:14:56,100
and my parents happened to be on a journey,

238
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,710
Mr. Xia had no other choice but to take me here.

239
00:14:59,030 --> 00:15:01,510
People who intend to ruin others' relationships

240
00:15:01,510 --> 00:15:04,070
are born with accidents.

241
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:06,020
What on earth do you mean?

242
00:15:06,020 --> 00:15:07,410
How can you speak for her!

243
00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:08,310
If my memory serves me right,

244
00:15:08,310 --> 00:15:09,620
you have a boyfriend, right?

245
00:15:09,990 --> 00:15:12,150
Weren't you going
to meet your boyfriend yesterday?

246
00:15:12,150 --> 00:15:13,840
Why did you run into accidents?

247
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:14,940
You didn't ask your boyfriend for help

248
00:15:14,940 --> 00:15:16,960
but stayed overnight at another man's house.

249
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,580
Are relationships today

250
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:20,400
all casual like this?

251
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:22,320
My boyfriend...

252
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:24,880
Shen Qing, you shouldn't have taken it out on her.

253
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:28,290
Hurry up to prepare breakfast for your son.

254
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:32,400
Change the pajama.

255
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:50,470
Well,

256
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,010
enjoy yourself. I'll go back now.

257
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:54,550
Without breakfast?

258
00:15:57,980 --> 00:16:00,230
I don't eat breakfast.

259
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:04,080
Miss, your stomach is growling.

260
00:16:05,090 --> 00:16:06,710
Since nothing happened,

261
00:16:06,710 --> 00:16:07,830
why don't you stay to have breakfast?

262
00:16:08,660 --> 00:16:09,680
Just sit there and have breakfast,

263
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:11,120
or she won't stop.

264
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:22,530
Milk or coffee?

265
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:24,470
Both are okay.

266
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:31,260
Thank you.

267
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,720
What brings you here today?

268
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:37,120
The nanny asked for leave today.

269
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:39,170
So Xiaoxi needs to stay at your home today.

270
00:16:40,740 --> 00:16:43,120
Mr. Xia's illegitimate child?

271
00:16:44,610 --> 00:16:46,310
He is so good-looking,

272
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,530
in which way he looks a bit like Mr. Xia.

273
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:53,110
Miss, why were you staring at me?

274
00:16:54,740 --> 00:16:56,100
I... My eyes itch.

275
00:16:56,380 --> 00:16:58,290
What's your job?

276
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:00,390
I'm a original animation artist

277
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:01,720
and in charge of game planning now.

278
00:17:02,220 --> 00:17:03,280
What does that mean?

279
00:17:03,580 --> 00:17:04,660
I draw things.

280
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,590
Can you draw me a Peppa Pig?

